The article is a letter from former President Barack Obama to the Speaker of the House of Representatives and the President of the Senate. The letter states that the national emergency with respect to Sudan, which was declared in 1997 and expanded in 2006, will continue beyond November 3, 2016. The actions and policies of the Government of Sudan continue to pose a threat to the national security and foreign policy of the United States. Therefore, it is deemed necessary to continue the national emergency.